<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="121" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1305,2016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1305,1332]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cercus ventrally with numerous black, thick spines of which apical ones longer and somewhat sinuate (
<figureCitation box="[160,252,1341,1368]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1684,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hirtodrosophila zhangae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06470; N−P: paratype 06474). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrola- teral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral serrated projection); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca (red arrow point at apical indentation)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253628/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus apically with large membranous process which tapering distally in lateral view, subapically swollen dorsally, with a pair of lateral processes and ventral fin-shaped, marginally serrated process (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1335,1377,1404]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1684,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hirtodrosophila zhangae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06470; N−P: paratype 06474). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrola- teral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral serrated projection); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca (red arrow point at apical indentation)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253628/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
I–K, M); lateral processes small, flat, bent ventrad, finely serrate on dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[966,1082,1413,1440]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1684,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hirtodrosophila zhangae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06470; N−P: paratype 06474). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrola- teral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral serrated projection); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca (red arrow point at apical indentation)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253628/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Fig. 
<date box="[1017,1042,1414,1440]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">8I</date>
, M
</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal capsule apically indented (
<figureCitation box="[263,348,1449,1476]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1684,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,181,1664]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hirtodrosophila zhangae sp. nov. (A−M: holotype 06470; N−P: paratype 06474). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral view); D, cerci (ventral view); E, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); F, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, H, 10th sternite (anterior and ventral view, respectively); I−K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, sensilla of paramere (ventrola- teral view); M, aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at lateral process and ventral serrated projection); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca (red arrow point at apical indentation)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253628/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 8P</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1305,2016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1485,1512]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao, 2019" authorityName="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2019" box="[691,877,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minshanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[691,877,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">H. minshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[885,975,1486,1512]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[885,975,1486,1512]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount box="[1148,1171,1486,1512]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[1184,1204,1486,1512]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1432,1485,1512]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Figs 3A, B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,164,1521,1548]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1609,1634]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,849,1589]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,849,1589]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Head (anterior view), postocciput (posterior view), cibarium (dorsal and lateral view), and prementum (ventral and lateral view). A−F, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06474); G−L, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06471); M−R, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (paratype 06473)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415691/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">5</figureCitation>
A–F): Frontal vitta brown to dark brown, paler than front-orbital plate and ocellar triangle. Fronto-orbital plate dark brown. Ocellar setae inserted inside triangle made by ocelli. Face and facial carina dark brown. Gena brown, anteriorly dark brown. Subvibrissa weak, indistinguishable from other orals. Pedicel dark brown; first flagellomere grayish brown; arista with 4–5 dorsal branches. Supracervical setae 12–13 per side; postocular setae 22–24 per side. Cibarium with 6–7 medial and ca. 17 posterior sensilla per side. Prementum with five (one proximal, two lateral, and two distal) pairs of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1305,2016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[295,417,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 3A, B</figureCitation>
): Postpronotal lobe brown, paler than mesonotum. Mesonotum brown; lateral stripes indistinct. Notopleuron brown, somewhat paler than mesonotum. Thoracic pleura brown to dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1305,2016]" box="[199,798,1809,1836]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[276,398,1809,1836]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 3A, C</figureCitation>
): dm-cu crossvein slightly clouded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1305,2016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[268,355,1845,1872]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown to grayish yellow, tarsi distally grayish brown. First tarsomeres of all legs more or less shorter than total length of four succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1305,2016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[324,448,1917,1944]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Fig. 3A, D</figureCitation>
): Tergites pale yellow, with dark grayish brown caudal bands about 1/2 as wide as tergite which laterally expanded anteriad and medially interrupted. Sternites pale yellow, somewhat grayish; male sternite V slightly broader than others.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" startId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" targetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" targetPageId="9">
