<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,153,323]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis box="[199,297,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gupta &amp; Singh, 1981)" authorityName="Gupta &amp; Singh" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Gupta &amp; Singh" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[673,1115,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neomakinoi">
<emphasis box="[673,841,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">H. neomakinoi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gupta, J. P. &amp; Singh, O. P." box="[857,1107,153,179]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" pagination="33 - 39" refId="ref12679" refString="Gupta, J. P. &amp; Singh, O. P. (1981) Two new and two known species of Drosophila from Rimbick, West Bengal, India. Entomon, 6 (1), 33 - 39." type="journal article" year="1981">Gupta &amp; Singh, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having abdomen tergites with caudal bands laterally expanded and medially interrupted, cercus with short spines, small lateral processes of aedeagus, and apical shape of oviscapt, but can be distinguished from it by longitudinal stripes on mesonotum (unicolorous, shiny in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gupta &amp; Singh" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[410,577,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neomakinoi">
<emphasis box="[410,577,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">H. neomakinoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and dorsally swollen aedeagus with apical flat, membranous process and ventral serrated process (rod-shaped in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gupta &amp; Singh" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[592,757,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neomakinoi">
<emphasis box="[592,757,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">H. neomakinoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
